Male Travel Operations Coordinator
BAC Middle East
JLT, UAE
Posted on: 30 Apr 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
AED10,000
6 Day shift pattern working week
On behalf of our client a privately owned luxury travel company that is based in Dubai, we are looking to recruit a Male Travel Operations Coordinator.
Reporting to the CEO you will be responsible for providing a high level of global customer service to clients and suppliers across the world, process booking and confirmations with suppliers, track services with the supplier and liaise confirmations to the client with the utmost accuracy
REQUIREMENTS
Qualifications:
•The successful candidate must be a resident of the UEA,
•Have 2 years experience in either travel, chauffeur services, airport services,
•Be flexible with regards to working hours as the company has day and night shifts,
•Have excellent time management and organizational skills and be fluent in English
ABOUT THE COMPANY
BAC Middle East - the longest established professional recruitment consultancy in the UAE. Established in 1979, we have been at the forefront of the region's recruitment industry for 30 years and were the first firm of our type in the world to achieve ISO9001 certification: a reflection of our constant emphasis on quality and customer satisfaction.
With our well-developed infrastructure and staff strength, we are able to assist you with recruitment needs ranging from junior professionals through to middle and senior management, whatever your industry sector.
BAC's proven regional experience and resources can help ensure that you recruit the best available candidates and enjoy the many advantages of a managed recruitment process.
